&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Senior Research Portfolio Officers&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Band 7 &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;2 full time fixed term posts &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;One post to maternity leave for 6 months in the first instance&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;One post for 12 months&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;(Secondments considered)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are seeking enthusiastic and motivated individuals to actively engage and support partner organisations in becoming research active in line with our research strategy. The fixed term posts will cover several specialities. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The post holders will liaise, establish and maintain positive links with partner organisations to promote research in line with national and local targets. In order to increase the capacity and capability at sites to undertake research you will have an in-depth knowledge of the healthcare landscape.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Working with colleagues in North Thames partner organisations in hospital and primary/community care settings, you will assess the feasibility of studies ensuring they are best placed for maximum recruitment, as well as promote participation in NIHR adopted studies commercial and non- commercial.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The successful candidates will demonstrate:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A collaborative approach with excellent communication and influencing skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An understanding of the changing landscape in health care settings&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Personal credibility that generates the trust of a wide group of internal and external stakeholders&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;For further details please contact:-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Aryana Chopra &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;aryana.chopra@nihr.ac.uk&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt; – for 6 month post&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Robert Pleass &lt;/span&gt;robert.pleass@nihr.ac.uk&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt; – for 12 month post&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Closing Date: 1 November 2020&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
